1
00:00:03,805 --> 00:00:04,773
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:04,773 --> 00:00:06,174
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:06,174 --> 00:00:07,242
(Scenes with child actors
followed production guidelines.)

4
00:00:11,313 --> 00:00:14,249
May I ask about...

5
00:00:15,183 --> 00:00:16,551
the new vision you're planning?

6
00:00:25,260 --> 00:00:26,595
Before I answer that,

7
00:00:27,462 --> 00:00:30,465
I need you to swear
absolute loyalty to me.

8
00:00:32,467 --> 00:00:33,635
Can you personally prove...

9
00:00:34,836 --> 00:00:36,605
that this path will save the village...

10
00:00:42,077 --> 00:00:45,213
and my family?

11
00:00:49,417 --> 00:00:52,220
Of course. I promise.

12
00:00:55,524 --> 00:00:58,226
It's a life-changing decision
for you and your family.

13
00:00:58,927 --> 00:01:00,362
You need the right tool to support it.

14
00:01:00,896 --> 00:01:01,730
Take it.

15
00:01:30,559 --> 00:01:32,160
You said that...

16
00:01:32,994 --> 00:01:34,329
your plan will save both Yeonri-ri...

17
00:01:34,863 --> 00:01:37,065
and my family, right?

18
00:01:55,951 --> 00:01:59,554
Please prove that promise.

19
00:02:07,662 --> 00:02:12,868
(EP 8 Betrayed by the Trusted Cabbage?)

20
00:02:12,868 --> 00:02:14,703
(Cafeteria)

21
00:02:14,703 --> 00:02:15,704
Hi.

22
00:02:15,971 --> 00:02:18,473
The burdock root... One box is missing.

23
00:02:19,441 --> 00:02:20,275
Yes.

24
00:02:21,009 --> 00:02:22,210
Thank you.

25
00:02:22,778 --> 00:02:23,779
Bye.

26
00:02:27,349 --> 00:02:28,550
(Order Sheet)

27
00:02:28,550 --> 00:02:30,886
It's complete chaos
when I have to order ingredients.

28
00:02:37,859 --> 00:02:40,428
Bo Mi, I'm going to Seoul.

29
00:02:59,080 --> 00:02:59,948
Bo Mi.

30
00:03:11,526 --> 00:03:14,129
I'm sorry, Bo Mi.
I got your clothes dirty.

31
00:03:16,431 --> 00:03:17,599
It's okay.

32
00:03:18,467 --> 00:03:20,402
I can wash it.

33
00:03:24,639 --> 00:03:26,007
Is it because of Ji Cheon?

34
00:03:29,444 --> 00:03:30,879
Earlier...

35
00:03:30,879 --> 00:03:34,749
I had something in my eye.

36
00:03:36,251 --> 00:03:37,452
You don't think...

37
00:03:37,452 --> 00:03:39,855
I was crying because of Ji Cheon, do you?

38
00:03:40,755 --> 00:03:44,226
It's not true. Not at all.

39
00:03:50,866 --> 00:03:52,000
I never thought...

40
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:55,237
you were crying because of Ji Cheon.

41
00:04:00,475 --> 00:04:02,210
I should get back to work now.

42
00:04:02,210 --> 00:04:04,112
It's quite late.

43
00:04:04,112 --> 00:04:06,681
You should get back to the station too.

44
00:04:07,649 --> 00:04:08,517
Bo Mi.

45
00:04:12,821 --> 00:04:14,623
I would never make the woman I like cry.

46
00:04:17,292 --> 00:04:19,461
Please remember that I'm here for you too.

47
00:04:30,705 --> 00:04:31,940
Should I wait outside?

48
00:04:34,075 --> 00:04:34,943
No.

49
00:04:50,425 --> 00:04:51,326
You're back.

50
00:04:52,894 --> 00:04:53,995
How did it go?

51
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:01,536
Did you talk to your professor?

52
00:05:03,305 --> 00:05:05,674
You told him...

53
00:05:05,674 --> 00:05:07,542
you're not dropping out, right?

54
00:05:10,679 --> 00:05:12,280
Why aren't you saying anything?

55
00:05:13,248 --> 00:05:14,983
Didn't you hear what I said?

56
00:05:15,851 --> 00:05:17,986
You're going back to school, right?

57
00:05:19,654 --> 00:05:20,555
Mom.

58
00:05:22,090 --> 00:05:23,024
I'm sorry.

59
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:27,596
Why?

60
00:05:29,564 --> 00:05:30,599
Why are you sorry?

61
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,268
I...

62
00:05:35,904 --> 00:05:37,139
officially dropped out of med school.

63
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:39,908
I'm not a med student anymore.

64
00:05:47,082 --> 00:05:47,949
Mom.

65
00:05:50,085 --> 00:05:50,986
Do you know...

66
00:05:51,686 --> 00:05:54,489
what I gave up to send you to med school?

67
00:05:56,124 --> 00:05:58,026
I gave up my entire life.

68
00:05:59,494 --> 00:06:00,529
Mom, I...

69
00:06:02,631 --> 00:06:03,799
We couldn't afford it,

70
00:06:04,766 --> 00:06:06,601
so I took out loans...

71
00:06:08,703 --> 00:06:10,038
to pay for your tutors.

72
00:06:11,506 --> 00:06:14,943
Do you know how many times I had to bow
my head at the bank counter?

73
00:06:15,777 --> 00:06:17,679
I had to call people over and over,

74
00:06:17,679 --> 00:06:20,315
begging, "Just this once."

75
00:06:21,283 --> 00:06:23,518
Do you know how miserable
that made me feel?

76
00:06:24,352 --> 00:06:27,456
I wanted to bite my tongue and die.

77
00:06:27,456 --> 00:06:29,724
That's why I tried my best to hang on.

78
00:06:30,625 --> 00:06:31,827
But Mom...

79
00:06:36,465 --> 00:06:37,899
I can't do this anymore.

80
00:06:38,366 --> 00:06:39,367
You can't?

81
00:06:41,069 --> 00:06:41,970
Then what about me?

82
00:06:44,106 --> 00:06:47,576
Then how am I supposed to live now?

83
00:06:49,845 --> 00:06:52,714
To ensure your bright future,

84
00:06:52,714 --> 00:06:54,883
I poured everything I had into you.

85
00:06:57,986 --> 00:07:00,555
How can my own child do this to me?

86
00:07:01,089 --> 00:07:03,458
How can you be so cruel to me?

87
00:07:05,660 --> 00:07:06,561
You...

88
00:07:07,395 --> 00:07:09,998
Are you really my son Ji Cheon?

89
00:07:09,998 --> 00:07:10,866
Are you?

90
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,068
Mom.

91
00:07:14,336 --> 00:07:15,470
If I'm not a doctor,

92
00:07:16,838 --> 00:07:18,473
am I not your son anymore?

93
00:07:18,907 --> 00:07:21,409
I'm doing all this...

94
00:07:21,409 --> 00:07:24,212
so you can live proudly and happily.

95
00:07:24,212 --> 00:07:25,147
Don't you get it?

96
00:07:30,685 --> 00:07:31,787
No, I don't get it.

97
00:07:33,588 --> 00:07:35,157
You're telling me to endure unhappiness.

98
00:07:39,194 --> 00:07:40,662
Is that really for me?

99
00:07:43,965 --> 00:07:45,300
I quit because it got too hard,

100
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:47,035
and I'm much happier now that I've quit.

101
00:07:49,638 --> 00:07:51,239
Is that really so wrong?

102
00:08:01,483 --> 00:08:02,484
I'm home.

103
00:08:40,021 --> 00:08:40,889
Honey.

104
00:08:42,023 --> 00:08:43,925
Imagine how tough it must've been for him.

105
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:47,429
Let him calm down first and...

106
00:08:47,429 --> 00:08:49,598
Is this someone else's problem to you?

107
00:08:50,165 --> 00:08:53,368
Your son just threw his life away!

108
00:08:54,035 --> 00:08:56,171
What do you mean?

109
00:08:56,171 --> 00:08:57,139
Life is long.

110
00:08:57,139 --> 00:08:59,875
Ji Cheon is only 23 years old.

111
00:09:00,142 --> 00:09:02,444
Yes, life is long.

112
00:09:02,444 --> 00:09:03,311
But...

113
00:09:03,678 --> 00:09:06,381
during all that time, what have you done?

114
00:09:06,782 --> 00:09:08,416
You just stood by and watched, didn't you?

115
00:09:08,416 --> 00:09:09,251
What?

116
00:09:10,552 --> 00:09:12,154
I just stood by and watched?

117
00:09:12,788 --> 00:09:13,722
Didn't you?

118
00:09:14,956 --> 00:09:18,493
I'm the one who handled
Ji Cheon's tutoring and studies.

119
00:09:18,493 --> 00:09:20,128
While I was in Canada with the kids,

120
00:09:20,128 --> 00:09:21,696
what were you doing?

121
00:09:23,198 --> 00:09:26,168
When I was crying all night because
I couldn't speak a word of English,

122
00:09:26,768 --> 00:09:28,370
when Ji Gu was sick,

123
00:09:28,370 --> 00:09:30,972
or when Ji Sang was causing trouble,
what were you doing?

124
00:09:31,740 --> 00:09:33,608
You thought that just sending money
from Korea...

125
00:09:33,608 --> 00:09:35,844
meant you'd done your part, didn't you?

126
00:09:35,844 --> 00:09:38,013
I worked myself to the bone
here in Korea...

127
00:09:38,413 --> 00:09:40,449
to earn that money.

128
00:09:40,849 --> 00:09:44,286
So you and the kids can live comfortably.

129
00:09:44,286 --> 00:09:45,220
Comfortably?

130
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:49,057
I had to handle everything...

131
00:09:49,057 --> 00:09:51,893
from their education, meals,
insurance to housing.

132
00:09:52,527 --> 00:09:55,130
I had to make all those
nerve-wracking decisions by myself.

133
00:09:56,565 --> 00:09:57,899
Every time,

134
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,936
you told me to decide on my own.

135
00:10:01,636 --> 00:10:03,438
Did my opinion ever actually matter?

136
00:10:03,772 --> 00:10:07,008
When it came to the kids,
it always went your way.

137
00:10:07,008 --> 00:10:07,876
My way?

138
00:10:08,310 --> 00:10:11,146
Trying to do what's best for the kids...
You call that my way?

139
00:10:18,553 --> 00:10:19,921
When Ji Cheon was born,

140
00:10:21,490 --> 00:10:22,858
what did you say?

141
00:10:24,826 --> 00:10:26,962
You said we'd protect him together.

142
00:10:28,430 --> 00:10:29,364
But now,

143
00:10:31,867 --> 00:10:33,135
it feels like...

144
00:10:33,635 --> 00:10:35,771
I'm the only one keeping that promise.

145
00:10:38,874 --> 00:10:41,409
Why do I have to be the bad mother?

146
00:10:43,712 --> 00:10:45,347
Why do you just stand by,

147
00:10:46,948 --> 00:10:49,117
acting composed, and doing nothing?

148
00:10:51,319 --> 00:10:52,187
I...

149
00:10:53,722 --> 00:10:55,090
can't leave Ji Cheon like this.

150
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:00,362
If no one else will, I'll step up
and do what's right.

151
00:11:03,431 --> 00:11:04,332
Honey.

152
00:11:04,766 --> 00:11:05,634
Honey.

153
00:11:06,435 --> 00:11:08,670
Seong Ji Cheon. Come back out here.

154
00:11:08,670 --> 00:11:11,239
- Let's talk.
- Honey, please.

155
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:13,842
This is all because of you.

156
00:11:13,842 --> 00:11:16,044
What do you want me to do?

157
00:11:16,044 --> 00:11:18,046
I told you. Let's go back to Seoul.

158
00:11:20,015 --> 00:11:22,050
Let's take Ji Cheon
and move back to Seoul.

159
00:11:22,050 --> 00:11:23,885
I've been saying this from the beginning.

160
00:11:26,021 --> 00:11:28,890
Because of who do you think
we're all here,

161
00:11:29,424 --> 00:11:31,460
suffering like this?

162
00:11:31,460 --> 00:11:32,928
Please!

163
00:11:34,463 --> 00:11:36,498
The more you act like this,
the more suffocated I feel.

164
00:11:36,498 --> 00:11:38,633
Don't you see
that the kids feel suffocated too?

165
00:11:41,069 --> 00:11:41,937
Everything's fine.

166
00:11:44,372 --> 00:11:45,273
Yeah?

167
00:11:47,209 --> 00:11:48,110
I see.

168
00:11:49,711 --> 00:11:50,612
I've been the one...

169
00:11:51,313 --> 00:11:53,949
suffocating the whole family, haven't I?

170
00:11:56,017 --> 00:11:56,785
You're right.

171
00:11:57,953 --> 00:11:59,187
I ruined everyone.

172
00:11:59,187 --> 00:12:00,622
No, honey.

173
00:12:00,622 --> 00:12:01,723
That's not what I meant.

174
00:12:01,723 --> 00:12:03,225
Honey, you see...

175
00:12:54,810 --> 00:12:55,744
Honey?

176
00:12:57,078 --> 00:12:58,046
Honey.

177
00:12:59,614 --> 00:13:00,882
She's already up?

178
00:13:20,068 --> 00:13:21,503
Where are her cosmetics?

179
00:13:26,441 --> 00:13:27,709
Where are all her clothes?

180
00:13:28,743 --> 00:13:29,644
What?

181
00:13:39,187 --> 00:13:40,956
Go ahead and do it your way.

182
00:13:40,956 --> 00:13:44,292
Try raising and educating the kids
on your own here for once.

183
00:13:47,929 --> 00:13:50,398
This isn't right, Cho Mi Ryeo.

184
00:13:54,503 --> 00:13:55,570
Honey.

185
00:13:59,341 --> 00:14:00,275
Cho Mi Ryeo.

186
00:14:01,309 --> 00:14:02,144
Honey.

187
00:14:03,745 --> 00:14:05,714
Mi Ryeo. Honey.

188
00:14:05,714 --> 00:14:06,782
Honey.

189
00:14:17,159 --> 00:14:18,760
Answer the phone.

190
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:21,496
The person you're calling
is not available right now.

191
00:14:24,699 --> 00:14:25,767
I want to be...

192
00:14:26,368 --> 00:14:28,370
a proper father and husband too.

193
00:14:29,004 --> 00:14:30,639
But how can you move out like this?

194
00:14:30,639 --> 00:14:31,840
You don't even have anywhere to go.

195
00:14:32,941 --> 00:14:33,909
Cho Mi Ryeo.

196
00:14:34,209 --> 00:14:35,343
Honey.

197
00:15:07,442 --> 00:15:08,777
(My hubby)

198
00:15:08,777 --> 00:15:11,313
Just tell me where you are.

199
00:15:11,313 --> 00:15:12,747
I'm worried about you.

200
00:15:19,788 --> 00:15:23,825
(7:00 AM alarm)

201
00:15:28,897 --> 00:15:30,532
I wonder if the kids are up.

202
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:33,902
They had a lot of supplies
to take to school today.

203
00:15:39,608 --> 00:15:41,777
Mom. We're out of toothpaste.

204
00:16:01,229 --> 00:16:02,664
You still haven't found it?

205
00:16:03,465 --> 00:16:05,267
Are you playing hide-and-seek
with toothpaste?

206
00:16:05,667 --> 00:16:07,469
Do we even have more toothpaste?

207
00:16:08,036 --> 00:16:10,138
Just say you give up or something.

208
00:16:11,873 --> 00:16:13,742
This is when we need Mom's magic.

209
00:16:14,576 --> 00:16:16,278
She'd find it right away.

210
00:16:16,278 --> 00:16:17,679
Mom, where's...

211
00:16:18,613 --> 00:16:19,481
Wait.

212
00:16:19,915 --> 00:16:20,949
Ji Sang.

213
00:16:21,583 --> 00:16:23,852
You should eat first.

214
00:16:23,852 --> 00:16:25,954
I'll find it for you while you're eating.

215
00:16:25,954 --> 00:16:27,088
Wait.

216
00:16:27,088 --> 00:16:29,124
Why are you cooking breakfast?

217
00:16:30,258 --> 00:16:32,427
I...

218
00:16:33,295 --> 00:16:34,596
Mom.

219
00:16:53,548 --> 00:16:55,383
Unbelievable.

220
00:16:56,351 --> 00:16:57,185
I'm sorry.

221
00:16:57,185 --> 00:16:59,855
It looks like you'll have to go to school
without eating breakfast.

222
00:16:59,855 --> 00:17:01,656
That might be better.

223
00:17:02,390 --> 00:17:04,126
We can't even brush our teeth.

224
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:07,929
Dad, my hair.

225
00:17:08,897 --> 00:17:09,831
What do I need to do?

226
00:17:14,536 --> 00:17:15,637
- Dad.
- Yes?

227
00:17:15,637 --> 00:17:17,339
Where did Mom go?

228
00:17:17,906 --> 00:17:20,408
Well, she...

229
00:17:21,443 --> 00:17:25,147
She urgently had to...

230
00:17:26,114 --> 00:17:26,915
You see?

231
00:17:27,449 --> 00:17:28,717
She...

232
00:17:29,785 --> 00:17:32,621
had to go to the house
of a really distant relative.

233
00:17:32,621 --> 00:17:34,956
Like your grandmother's grandmother's.

234
00:17:36,091 --> 00:17:38,727
Anyway, Mom won't be around
for a few days,

235
00:17:38,727 --> 00:17:41,096
so let's try to manage together, okay?

236
00:17:41,530 --> 00:17:43,532
You're going to be late.

237
00:17:43,932 --> 00:17:47,269
Make sure you eat enough at lunch...

238
00:17:47,269 --> 00:17:49,671
that you won't want dinner later.
Okay, kids?

239
00:17:49,671 --> 00:17:50,672
Eat two bowls of rice each.

240
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:14,262
Mom moved out because of me, didn't she?

241
00:18:14,963 --> 00:18:16,198
No.

242
00:18:16,198 --> 00:18:18,500
Why would she move out? She's not a kid.

243
00:18:19,568 --> 00:18:22,304
If anyone should leave,
it should be me. Why Mom?

244
00:18:22,304 --> 00:18:24,406
Mom would faint if she heard that.

245
00:18:24,873 --> 00:18:26,007
Just stay put.

246
00:18:26,007 --> 00:18:28,009
She'll be back once she cools down.

247
00:18:28,677 --> 00:18:29,578
Go.

248
00:18:38,487 --> 00:18:41,923
(Nutrition Room)

249
00:19:00,175 --> 00:19:01,076
Bo Mi.

250
00:19:04,646 --> 00:19:05,514
Let go of me.

251
00:19:08,884 --> 00:19:11,153
I made you wait a long time, didn't I?
I'm sorry.

252
00:19:11,753 --> 00:19:12,821
Mr. Seong Ji Cheon.

253
00:19:13,989 --> 00:19:15,657
This is a workplace.

254
00:19:16,424 --> 00:19:18,727
Just because it's a small rural school
with a few students...

255
00:19:19,094 --> 00:19:21,496
doesn't mean you can come and go
as you please.

256
00:19:21,496 --> 00:19:23,198
I'm really sorry about that.

257
00:19:23,198 --> 00:19:24,866
But I really had to go to Seoul.

258
00:19:24,866 --> 00:19:26,034
If you're going to be like this,

259
00:19:27,102 --> 00:19:28,136
just quit now.

260
00:19:28,970 --> 00:19:29,838
What?

261
00:19:31,873 --> 00:19:32,808
Bo Mi.

262
00:19:41,116 --> 00:19:43,351
At least come in and try to explain
or something.

263
00:19:53,962 --> 00:19:54,896
Bo Mi.

264
00:19:55,564 --> 00:19:57,265
I don't want to quit this job.

265
00:19:58,567 --> 00:20:01,203
I never looked down on this school
just because it's in the countryside.

266
00:20:01,803 --> 00:20:04,806
I really enjoy working with you, Bo Mi.

267
00:20:05,740 --> 00:20:07,542
The best thing I've done
since coming here...

268
00:20:08,910 --> 00:20:10,879
is working with you at this school.

269
00:20:18,186 --> 00:20:19,287
Do you have anything to say...

270
00:20:19,888 --> 00:20:21,056
besides that?

271
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:23,191
What?

272
00:20:23,558 --> 00:20:25,060
You disappeared without a word,

273
00:20:25,060 --> 00:20:27,429
didn't respond at all,
and then suddenly showed up.

274
00:20:28,096 --> 00:20:30,365
I disappeared without a word?

275
00:20:30,832 --> 00:20:33,535
Didn't you get my text?

276
00:20:34,402 --> 00:20:37,773
I told you that I'd be back soon.

277
00:20:44,112 --> 00:20:45,147
Ji Cheon.

278
00:20:47,983 --> 00:20:49,184
Message not sent.

279
00:20:49,785 --> 00:20:50,852
Don't you see this?

280
00:20:50,852 --> 00:20:51,787
Message not sent?

281
00:20:53,288 --> 00:20:54,156
What?

282
00:20:55,524 --> 00:20:56,424
How could this be?

283
00:20:57,959 --> 00:20:59,995
Bo Mi, I'm going to Seoul.

284
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:06,468
I'm sorry for ghosting you
these last few days.

285
00:21:07,235 --> 00:21:08,236
I'll see you when I get back.

286
00:21:15,243 --> 00:21:16,211
I...

287
00:21:16,678 --> 00:21:18,346
really didn't know.

288
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:19,948
I'm really sorry.

289
00:21:19,948 --> 00:21:20,949
Hold on.

290
00:21:23,885 --> 00:21:24,853
I...

291
00:21:25,387 --> 00:21:27,989
Bo Mi, it's a misunderstanding.

292
00:21:27,989 --> 00:21:29,558
I get why you'd think that,

293
00:21:29,558 --> 00:21:30,826
but this is a misunderstanding.

294
00:21:30,826 --> 00:21:31,993
I didn't know.

295
00:21:31,993 --> 00:21:34,930
I don't know what happened. Why did it...

296
00:21:34,930 --> 00:21:35,931
I thought the text was sent.

297
00:21:35,931 --> 00:21:38,100
I am so sorry. I didn't know.

298
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:40,569
Where would I even go?

299
00:21:40,569 --> 00:21:41,703
I don't have anywhere to go.

300
00:21:53,048 --> 00:21:54,249
You were quite upset, weren't you?

301
00:21:57,719 --> 00:21:59,254
Do you even have to ask?

302
00:22:01,089 --> 00:22:03,258
It made me wonder if this is all we were
to each other.

303
00:22:04,993 --> 00:22:05,927
I thought...

304
00:22:07,295 --> 00:22:09,598
we'd gotten pretty close.

305
00:22:11,366 --> 00:22:13,869
We did get close.

306
00:22:15,303 --> 00:22:16,171
What?

307
00:22:18,774 --> 00:22:19,908
Did you miss me?

308
00:22:22,344 --> 00:22:23,378
You.

309
00:22:23,845 --> 00:22:25,981
You went to Seoul and came back all bold.

310
00:22:29,951 --> 00:22:32,554
I dropped out of med school.

311
00:22:34,422 --> 00:22:37,259
I met with my professor,
signed the papers, and it's done.

312
00:22:40,162 --> 00:22:41,062
I'm not...

313
00:22:43,698 --> 00:22:44,900
a med student anymore.

314
00:22:47,536 --> 00:22:48,503
You did well.

315
00:22:50,672 --> 00:22:52,040
You finally climbed over the wall.

316
00:22:53,942 --> 00:22:55,844
I'll tell you that...

317
00:22:56,344 --> 00:22:58,380
what you did was both the bravest
and dumbest thing in the world.

318
00:22:59,381 --> 00:23:00,282
You did well.

319
00:23:04,352 --> 00:23:05,187
As expected.

320
00:23:06,488 --> 00:23:09,090
You always say things like that.

321
00:23:10,859 --> 00:23:14,763
I wish other people saw it that way too.

322
00:23:17,332 --> 00:23:19,801
Your mom was quite angry, wasn't she?

323
00:23:22,838 --> 00:23:23,772
My mom...

324
00:23:26,441 --> 00:23:28,310
thinks that beyond the wall is hell.

325
00:23:29,845 --> 00:23:31,480
The more courage I show,

326
00:23:34,182 --> 00:23:36,284
the more it feels like
her world is falling apart.

327
00:23:38,386 --> 00:23:40,021
It may take time,

328
00:23:40,922 --> 00:23:41,890
but someday...

329
00:23:43,458 --> 00:23:44,860
she'll understand.

330
00:23:49,264 --> 00:23:50,432
I don't know.

331
00:23:53,568 --> 00:23:55,704
My mom left us.

332
00:24:00,609 --> 00:24:02,210
I got the kids to school.

333
00:24:03,078 --> 00:24:04,346
I won't ask you to come back home.

334
00:24:04,346 --> 00:24:05,614
Just tell me where you are.

335
00:24:06,882 --> 00:24:09,251
Once you've cooled off,
will you reply with a period at least?

336
00:24:10,118 --> 00:24:11,052
Do you have money?

337
00:24:12,621 --> 00:24:14,689
Let's see how you all do without me.

338
00:24:14,689 --> 00:24:15,757
Good luck.

339
00:24:19,694 --> 00:24:21,329
I should go eat now.

340
00:24:22,597 --> 00:24:23,465
This looks so good, Hye Sun.

341
00:24:23,465 --> 00:24:25,700
I heard they remodeled this place.

342
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:27,169
It's much cleaner and nicer now.

343
00:24:27,169 --> 00:24:28,904
Let's go this way.
Should we go sit over there?

344
00:24:28,904 --> 00:24:30,572
Why is it so crowded?

345
00:24:36,878 --> 00:24:38,713
They even added lights over there.

346
00:24:39,781 --> 00:24:40,715
Let's sit here.

347
00:24:40,715 --> 00:24:43,518
We must plop down on the floor
like this and eat.

348
00:24:44,386 --> 00:24:46,188
- Goodness.
- My back.

349
00:24:46,188 --> 00:24:48,557
This is the stuff, Hye Sun.

350
00:24:49,558 --> 00:24:50,692
Did you confirm it?

351
00:24:51,593 --> 00:24:53,495
- You're ignoring me again?
- Eat up.

352
00:24:55,997 --> 00:24:57,499
That's them.

353
00:24:57,499 --> 00:24:58,767
What are they doing here?

354
00:25:02,237 --> 00:25:03,138
What do I do?

355
00:25:04,473 --> 00:25:05,440
It's nothing.

356
00:25:10,545 --> 00:25:11,746
How funny.

357
00:25:20,122 --> 00:25:21,389
What do I do?

358
00:25:21,857 --> 00:25:23,892
How can I run into them here?

359
00:25:24,526 --> 00:25:25,961
Eat up.

360
00:25:25,961 --> 00:25:27,295
It looks so good.

361
00:25:27,295 --> 00:25:28,363
Right.

362
00:25:29,331 --> 00:25:30,932
- This is bad.
- What is?

363
00:25:30,932 --> 00:25:32,634
We forgot to get fish cake.

364
00:25:32,634 --> 00:25:35,670
We must have that to complete this meal.

365
00:25:35,670 --> 00:25:38,106
We must eat before it gets soggy, though.

366
00:25:38,106 --> 00:25:39,841
We'll eat this first and buy one later.

367
00:25:39,841 --> 00:25:41,476
- Would you like some kimchi?
- Yes.

368
00:25:41,476 --> 00:25:42,410
I'll go get some kimchi.

369
00:25:42,410 --> 00:25:44,713
Yes, go ask them, Hye Sun.
I'll be here eating.

370
00:25:46,081 --> 00:25:48,216
Excuse me. Kimchi...

371
00:25:49,284 --> 00:25:50,919
You gave us kimchi last time.

372
00:25:52,053 --> 00:25:54,189
Don't run your business like this.

373
00:25:54,189 --> 00:25:55,924
It's so cumbersome.

374
00:25:55,924 --> 00:25:57,959
- They don't have kimchi?
- They don't.

375
00:25:57,959 --> 00:25:59,995
- Can you please close this door?
- They only gave us pickled radish?

376
00:25:59,995 --> 00:26:00,862
Hurry.

377
00:26:03,098 --> 00:26:05,300
The hot sauna room. Our next step.

378
00:26:05,300 --> 00:26:06,401
Take it easy.

379
00:26:06,401 --> 00:26:08,670
Don't try to beat me
and pass out like last time.

380
00:26:08,670 --> 00:26:11,506
I wasn't in the best condition back then.

381
00:26:13,308 --> 00:26:14,075
Go.

382
00:26:14,075 --> 00:26:15,110
My goodness.

383
00:26:15,811 --> 00:26:16,711
Gosh.

384
00:26:18,547 --> 00:26:20,649
Look. It's Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo.

385
00:26:20,649 --> 00:26:21,883
What are you doing here?

386
00:26:21,883 --> 00:26:23,418
Look at all that sweat.

387
00:26:23,418 --> 00:26:24,619
Are you okay?

388
00:26:25,086 --> 00:26:29,124
Your face is cooked red like a boiled egg.

389
00:26:29,624 --> 00:26:31,426
Why were you being so foolish
staying in there for so long?

390
00:26:31,426 --> 00:26:33,295
You should've done it moderately.

391
00:26:33,295 --> 00:26:35,130
Don't you need to go see a doctor?

392
00:26:35,130 --> 00:26:37,032
Leave her alone.

393
00:26:37,032 --> 00:26:38,500
She's got a great doctor son at home.

394
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:40,068
I'm sure he'll take good care of her.

395
00:26:40,068 --> 00:26:41,303
Right. Her son is a doctor.

396
00:26:41,670 --> 00:26:43,338
You don't know anything.

397
00:26:46,775 --> 00:26:50,112
To think what I went through to raise him!

398
00:26:53,348 --> 00:26:54,816
What's wrong with her?

399
00:26:54,816 --> 00:26:57,385
- Get up.
- What?

400
00:26:57,385 --> 00:26:58,687
You're blocking the door.

401
00:27:01,623 --> 00:27:02,757
My goodness.

402
00:27:02,757 --> 00:27:03,859
What's wrong with her?

403
00:27:05,427 --> 00:27:06,695
We don't know her.

404
00:27:07,629 --> 00:27:11,566
(Sauna entrance)

405
00:27:14,436 --> 00:27:17,038
Do you have a place to stay at?

406
00:27:18,373 --> 00:27:19,641
Of course.

407
00:27:21,009 --> 00:27:23,812
I know plenty of people in Seoul.

408
00:27:24,146 --> 00:27:25,013
I see.

409
00:27:25,914 --> 00:27:28,316
Then go on your way.

410
00:27:28,817 --> 00:27:29,785
Bye.

411
00:27:29,785 --> 00:27:30,652
But...

412
00:27:31,953 --> 00:27:33,688
it's really late right now.

413
00:27:34,823 --> 00:27:37,559
I feel bad about calling someone
to drive me.

414
00:27:41,730 --> 00:27:43,031
Come stay at our house.

415
00:27:44,366 --> 00:27:46,435
But...

416
00:27:47,536 --> 00:27:49,571
How could I possibly do that?

417
00:27:50,071 --> 00:27:51,873
Then...

418
00:27:51,873 --> 00:27:53,375
you can just go back in here.

419
00:27:53,742 --> 00:27:58,246
Even though all the ladies saw you...

420
00:27:58,246 --> 00:28:00,882
lying there crying your heart out.

421
00:28:00,882 --> 00:28:02,017
Right, Seon Ja?

422
00:28:02,017 --> 00:28:04,486
They'll feel bad for you and probably
buy you some eggs.

423
00:28:04,486 --> 00:28:05,587
You won't starve at least.

424
00:28:08,723 --> 00:28:10,959
What was that? It wasn't me.

425
00:28:12,260 --> 00:28:15,030
Come on. Come to our place.

426
00:28:18,533 --> 00:28:19,768
What is it?

427
00:28:22,771 --> 00:28:25,006
This is Mak Dung's stroller.

428
00:28:25,006 --> 00:28:27,709
Why are you trying to take it? Don't.

429
00:28:28,009 --> 00:28:30,212
- This is my suitcase.
- What are you doing?

430
00:28:30,212 --> 00:28:31,746
- No.
- What are you doing here?

431
00:28:31,746 --> 00:28:33,682
This is Mak Dung's.

432
00:28:33,949 --> 00:28:35,350
No, this is mine.

433
00:28:35,350 --> 00:28:37,752
- Mak Rae. This isn't yours.
- No.

434
00:28:37,752 --> 00:28:39,588
Where are her sisters?

435
00:28:39,588 --> 00:28:41,123
It's Mak Dung's.

436
00:28:41,623 --> 00:28:42,657
All right, Mak Rae.

437
00:28:42,657 --> 00:28:45,460
Do you want me to help you take it?

438
00:28:46,094 --> 00:28:47,562
Get up, Mak Rae.

439
00:28:47,562 --> 00:28:49,931
Get up. Yes.

440
00:28:49,931 --> 00:28:51,433
Shall we take Mak Dung's stuff and go?

441
00:28:51,433 --> 00:28:53,769
- Yes.
- Let's go.

442
00:28:53,769 --> 00:28:55,137
This is Mak Dung's stroller.

443
00:28:56,104 --> 00:28:57,139
Okay.

444
00:28:57,139 --> 00:28:58,373
Let's go, Mak Rae.

445
00:29:03,478 --> 00:29:05,814
The person you're calling...

446
00:29:08,617 --> 00:29:09,818
Is she really going to be like this?

447
00:29:19,427 --> 00:29:21,963
It's not like she has family here...

448
00:29:21,963 --> 00:29:23,298
Or friends.

449
00:29:24,900 --> 00:29:27,536
My wife moved out,
but there isn't a single place...

450
00:29:28,370 --> 00:29:29,704
I can call.

451
00:29:42,384 --> 00:29:43,318
Yes, Mr. Bae.

452
00:29:44,186 --> 00:29:45,287
Have you made your decision?

453
00:29:53,462 --> 00:29:55,497
Let's take Ji Cheon
and move back to Seoul.

454
00:29:55,497 --> 00:29:57,432
I've been saying this from the beginning.

455
00:29:58,033 --> 00:30:00,802
Because of who do you think
we're all here,

456
00:30:01,436 --> 00:30:04,473
suffering like this?

457
00:30:08,877 --> 00:30:10,045
Can you personally prove...

458
00:30:10,979 --> 00:30:12,814
that this path will save the village...

459
00:30:14,316 --> 00:30:17,519
and my family?

460
00:30:18,753 --> 00:30:21,056
Of course. I promise.

461
00:30:44,279 --> 00:30:46,748
I'll do it, Mr. Bae.

462
00:31:05,801 --> 00:31:06,635
You're home.

463
00:31:07,903 --> 00:31:08,770
Let's go inside.

464
00:31:20,081 --> 00:31:21,016
Mom...

465
00:31:22,083 --> 00:31:23,318
isn't answering your calls either, right?

466
00:31:24,052 --> 00:31:26,655
She won't even reply to my texts either.

467
00:31:29,591 --> 00:31:30,892
Dropping out of school...

468
00:31:32,494 --> 00:31:33,795
You thought it through, right?

469
00:31:34,796 --> 00:31:35,664
Yes.

470
00:31:36,498 --> 00:31:38,834
I made the decision after giving it
careful consideration.

471
00:31:41,369 --> 00:31:42,337
What's next?

472
00:31:46,141 --> 00:31:46,942
What?

473
00:31:48,043 --> 00:31:49,578
Dropping out isn't the end.

474
00:31:50,846 --> 00:31:52,280
This is just the beginning for you.

475
00:31:54,015 --> 00:31:55,517
Whatever you do here,

476
00:31:56,184 --> 00:31:59,454
people have their own place here.

477
00:32:02,757 --> 00:32:03,859
Think carefully...

478
00:32:05,494 --> 00:32:06,595
about what you're going to do.

479
00:32:21,176 --> 00:32:22,010
Come in.

480
00:32:31,553 --> 00:32:32,788
No one's home.

481
00:32:33,755 --> 00:32:34,656
Well...

482
00:32:35,857 --> 00:32:38,860
I don't think this is right.

483
00:32:39,761 --> 00:32:41,463
Then...

484
00:32:41,463 --> 00:32:44,366
Do you want to go back to your place?

485
00:32:50,872 --> 00:32:52,107
Come this way.

486
00:32:52,107 --> 00:32:53,108
This is the living room.

487
00:32:53,875 --> 00:32:55,644
Okay.

488
00:32:55,644 --> 00:32:56,778
Please excuse me.

489
00:32:56,778 --> 00:32:58,513
Sure.

490
00:32:58,914 --> 00:33:00,382
Come in.

491
00:33:04,753 --> 00:33:06,922
Spinach.

492
00:33:06,922 --> 00:33:07,989
Bracken.

493
00:33:11,693 --> 00:33:15,464
We've sweated it out,
so we need to fill it back up.

494
00:33:19,501 --> 00:33:22,237
Come and try some.

495
00:33:28,944 --> 00:33:30,378
It's so savory.

496
00:33:31,279 --> 00:33:32,414
The sesame oil...

497
00:33:33,081 --> 00:33:35,750
is especially amazing today.

498
00:33:38,687 --> 00:33:39,988
Come here.

499
00:33:40,288 --> 00:33:41,156
Come and have some...

500
00:33:42,958 --> 00:33:44,259
or I'll end up finishing this
all by myself.

501
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:46,261
Come on.

502
00:33:47,262 --> 00:33:48,330
Open up.

503
00:33:49,064 --> 00:33:49,898
Open up.

504
00:33:50,265 --> 00:33:51,700
It's too much.

505
00:33:55,103 --> 00:33:56,872
Was it too much?

506
00:33:58,573 --> 00:33:59,541
Goodness.

507
00:34:00,275 --> 00:34:01,409
Thank you.

508
00:34:07,516 --> 00:34:08,416
It's good, isn't it?

509
00:34:09,251 --> 00:34:10,652
Eat up.

510
00:34:12,754 --> 00:34:14,322
When your mind is unsettled,

511
00:34:14,956 --> 00:34:16,191
this is the best medicine.

512
00:34:17,058 --> 00:34:17,993
Have some more.

513
00:34:34,876 --> 00:34:37,145
Ta-da.

514
00:34:37,913 --> 00:34:39,347
Try it on.

515
00:34:40,248 --> 00:34:42,984
It's so comfortable,
it's like you're not wearing anything.

516
00:34:43,418 --> 00:34:44,886
No.

517
00:34:44,886 --> 00:34:46,922
I'll just wait for my suitcase.

518
00:34:46,922 --> 00:34:48,190
Goodness.

519
00:34:48,356 --> 00:34:51,293
Mak Rae is sleeping
with the suitcase in her arms.

520
00:34:51,293 --> 00:34:54,296
She'll wake up and scream
if we take it away.

521
00:34:55,163 --> 00:34:57,899
Just let her keep it for today.

522
00:34:58,567 --> 00:35:01,369
But this place is right in front
of my house.

523
00:35:02,170 --> 00:35:03,505
Who runs away from home...

524
00:35:03,505 --> 00:35:05,807
and stays this close?

525
00:35:10,712 --> 00:35:11,847
So...

526
00:35:11,847 --> 00:35:14,816
you're finally admitting
that you ran away from home?

527
00:35:16,985 --> 00:35:20,322
Haven't you heard the saying,
"It's darkest under the lamp?"

528
00:35:20,689 --> 00:35:21,490
Haven't you?

529
00:35:21,490 --> 00:35:23,492
I'll get your suitcase back tomorrow,

530
00:35:24,159 --> 00:35:26,695
so just stay here for now.

531
00:35:29,965 --> 00:35:30,966
Retro.

532
00:35:46,982 --> 00:35:48,216
Could it be a bit too small?

533
00:35:56,558 --> 00:35:57,359
Goodness.

534
00:35:58,326 --> 00:35:59,494
You look good in them.

535
00:36:03,799 --> 00:36:05,300
Ms. Nam.

536
00:36:06,401 --> 00:36:07,803
I'm really sorry,

537
00:36:08,703 --> 00:36:11,072
but my kids...

538
00:36:13,241 --> 00:36:14,342
All this food...

539
00:36:14,876 --> 00:36:17,512
I made it for your boys at home.

540
00:36:17,512 --> 00:36:19,281
I don't know if they'll like it.

541
00:36:19,815 --> 00:36:21,116
Are you serious?

542
00:36:21,750 --> 00:36:22,818
Thank you.

543
00:36:23,919 --> 00:36:25,887
Does your youngest eat anchovies?

544
00:36:27,022 --> 00:36:28,790
Not really, but...

545
00:36:30,792 --> 00:36:31,960
If it's okay with you,

546
00:36:33,528 --> 00:36:36,598
can I try something instead?

547
00:36:36,832 --> 00:36:39,234
He'll eat it if it's inside rice balls.

548
00:36:39,935 --> 00:36:41,770
Rice balls? Hold on.

549
00:36:42,437 --> 00:36:44,706
Rice is in the cooker.

550
00:36:44,706 --> 00:36:46,241
Thank you.

551
00:36:46,241 --> 00:36:49,010
A spoonful of sesame salt.

552
00:36:49,010 --> 00:36:50,679
- Top-notch sesame oil.
- Okay.

553
00:36:53,048 --> 00:36:53,782
Good.

554
00:36:54,716 --> 00:36:56,618
Gently mix with your fingertips.

555
00:36:57,452 --> 00:37:00,055
Making sure it doesn't clump.

556
00:37:09,331 --> 00:37:10,532
Is she really...

557
00:37:11,566 --> 00:37:12,834
not coming back today?

558
00:37:18,907 --> 00:37:20,575
- Dad.
- Yes?

559
00:37:20,575 --> 00:37:21,810
I'm hungry.

560
00:37:22,644 --> 00:37:25,180
Yes. We should eat.

561
00:37:25,180 --> 00:37:27,382
I'll make you something good.

562
00:37:27,382 --> 00:37:28,717
Tell me what you want.

563
00:37:29,584 --> 00:37:32,154
The cream spaghetti Mom used to make.

564
00:37:32,521 --> 00:37:34,055
With lots of bacon.

565
00:37:36,625 --> 00:37:39,528
Cream spaghetti... Bacon...

566
00:37:50,972 --> 00:37:53,675
Does pasta usually swell up like this?

567
00:37:54,209 --> 00:37:55,310
Why is it getting so big?

568
00:38:09,991 --> 00:38:12,928
Mom's is full of sauce and moist.

569
00:38:16,631 --> 00:38:18,366
Well...

570
00:38:19,468 --> 00:38:22,471
Just try it. The ingredients
are top quality.

571
00:38:24,306 --> 00:38:25,140
Dad.

572
00:38:25,841 --> 00:38:27,442
I miss Mom.

573
00:38:29,144 --> 00:38:32,280
If you eat and sleep well,

574
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:33,982
Mom will come back soon. Okay?

575
00:38:35,584 --> 00:38:36,551
What do you think, Ji Sang?

576
00:38:37,018 --> 00:38:38,820
I may have made too much pasta,

577
00:38:38,820 --> 00:38:40,155
but it tastes perfect, right?

578
00:38:41,089 --> 00:38:43,325
This isn't some giant tray of spaghetti.

579
00:38:44,259 --> 00:38:45,694
Why is there so much?

580
00:38:46,595 --> 00:38:50,799
I always just cook for one,

581
00:38:50,799 --> 00:38:52,200
so I couldn't get the portions right.

582
00:38:53,168 --> 00:38:55,070
Is there anything else you want to eat?

583
00:38:56,071 --> 00:38:57,272
Mom's cooking.

584
00:38:58,306 --> 00:38:59,241
Me too.

585
00:39:05,380 --> 00:39:06,414
The rice balls...

586
00:39:07,015 --> 00:39:08,350
They'll eat the anchovies, right?

587
00:39:09,518 --> 00:39:11,586
I'm home.

588
00:39:13,255 --> 00:39:14,055
You're back.

589
00:39:16,625 --> 00:39:18,994
My dear Nam Hye Sun.

590
00:39:18,994 --> 00:39:20,362
Your husband is home.

591
00:39:26,968 --> 00:39:27,969
Come here for a second.

592
00:39:28,737 --> 00:39:29,671
Welcome.

593
00:39:31,106 --> 00:39:32,007
What's going on here?

594
00:39:32,908 --> 00:39:35,076
She ran away from home.

595
00:39:35,076 --> 00:39:35,911
What?

596
00:39:36,711 --> 00:39:37,779
She ran away.

597
00:39:40,115 --> 00:39:41,550
Does Seong Tae Hun know?

598
00:39:42,451 --> 00:39:44,853
If he finds out his wife left,
he'll be worried sick.

599
00:39:44,853 --> 00:39:48,323
Since when did you ever care
about his feelings?

600
00:39:49,090 --> 00:39:51,059
I guess your shoulder
is feeling better now?

601
00:39:52,761 --> 00:39:53,895
This is what we'll do.

602
00:39:54,863 --> 00:39:57,532
We won't tell her,

603
00:39:57,532 --> 00:39:58,900
but we'll inform her family.

604
00:40:00,268 --> 00:40:03,472
Would that be better?

605
00:40:03,472 --> 00:40:06,208
No. Just send her home.

606
00:40:06,208 --> 00:40:08,276
We shouldn't get involved
in someone else's marriage.

607
00:40:08,276 --> 00:40:09,644
And where am I supposed to sleep?

608
00:40:09,644 --> 00:40:10,645
Over there.

609
00:40:10,879 --> 00:40:13,515
You usually sleep well over there.
Like this.

610
00:40:14,116 --> 00:40:14,983
I do?

611
00:40:15,617 --> 00:40:17,119
The living room is spacious.

612
00:40:18,353 --> 00:40:21,356
And your heart is as wide as...

613
00:40:22,190 --> 00:40:23,291
the Pacific Ocean.

614
00:40:24,693 --> 00:40:25,694
By myself?

615
00:40:25,694 --> 00:40:26,595
Move aside.

616
00:40:28,530 --> 00:40:29,931
All packed?

617
00:40:29,931 --> 00:40:30,832
Give it to me.

618
00:40:31,299 --> 00:40:32,167
Darn.

619
00:40:47,149 --> 00:40:48,083
Ji Cheon.

620
00:40:48,483 --> 00:40:50,552
Your mother is at our house right now.

621
00:40:50,786 --> 00:40:52,487
You don't need to worry
about her too much.

622
00:40:58,860 --> 00:41:00,061
Anyone home?

623
00:41:00,495 --> 00:41:02,130
- Mom.
- Mom.

624
00:41:02,130 --> 00:41:04,199
What brings you here this evening?

625
00:41:06,234 --> 00:41:09,671
We had some leftover side dishes,
so I brought them.

626
00:41:10,138 --> 00:41:12,073
You're cooking dinner, aren't you?

627
00:41:12,073 --> 00:41:12,941
Yes.

628
00:41:14,009 --> 00:41:16,678
I tend to cook too much, you know.

629
00:41:16,678 --> 00:41:18,747
- Here you go.
- That's a lot of food.

630
00:41:24,085 --> 00:41:26,221
This looks just like Mom's rice balls.

631
00:41:26,721 --> 00:41:27,622
You're right.

632
00:41:33,929 --> 00:41:35,897
They taste the same too.

633
00:41:37,999 --> 00:41:39,601
Well...

634
00:41:42,871 --> 00:41:44,139
I'll get going now.

635
00:41:44,139 --> 00:41:45,173
Okay.

636
00:41:48,243 --> 00:41:49,611
Okay.

637
00:42:01,123 --> 00:42:04,126
My wife is at your place, isn't she?

638
00:42:04,126 --> 00:42:05,794
I'll go bring her back.

639
00:42:05,794 --> 00:42:07,295
Don't.

640
00:42:08,196 --> 00:42:09,798
At times like this,

641
00:42:09,798 --> 00:42:12,801
just pretend you don't know
and give her time.

642
00:42:12,801 --> 00:42:15,904
I don't want her to impose on you.

643
00:42:16,471 --> 00:42:18,807
Don't worry about us.

644
00:42:18,807 --> 00:42:20,575
Just handle the situation well.

645
00:42:20,575 --> 00:42:22,644
She must've been really upset...

646
00:42:22,644 --> 00:42:24,146
to leave home like that.

647
00:42:24,146 --> 00:42:25,280
Yes, I will.

648
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:26,715
Okay. Goodbye.

649
00:42:26,715 --> 00:42:28,450
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

650
00:42:28,450 --> 00:42:30,118
- I won't go far.
- Okay.

651
00:42:41,630 --> 00:42:42,464
Sleep.

652
00:42:51,573 --> 00:42:52,574
Come sit over here.

653
00:42:53,542 --> 00:42:55,510
- Come to bed.
- Okay.

654
00:42:59,714 --> 00:43:02,517
How were the kids?

655
00:43:02,517 --> 00:43:03,752
They weren't crying, were they?

656
00:43:05,620 --> 00:43:07,689
When they saw the rice balls,

657
00:43:08,356 --> 00:43:10,158
I think they realized right away.

658
00:43:12,828 --> 00:43:16,832
If anything, your husband looked terrible.

659
00:43:21,169 --> 00:43:22,504
He probably finally understands...

660
00:43:23,305 --> 00:43:25,674
how hard it is to take care of the kids.

661
00:43:27,008 --> 00:43:30,112
I'm just relieved the kids seem okay.

662
00:43:30,112 --> 00:43:31,346
Thank you so much.

663
00:43:32,180 --> 00:43:34,382
If you care about your kids that much,

664
00:43:34,950 --> 00:43:36,618
why did you run away?

665
00:43:39,988 --> 00:43:41,423
My husband said that...

666
00:43:42,691 --> 00:43:45,861
the way I do things suffocates the kids.

667
00:43:46,461 --> 00:43:47,762
Unbelievable.

668
00:43:48,363 --> 00:43:51,366
That's easy for him to say.

669
00:43:51,366 --> 00:43:54,669
There's no right or wrong way
to raise children.

670
00:43:54,669 --> 00:43:56,271
Exactly.

671
00:43:56,271 --> 00:43:58,807
Anyone can say nice things.

672
00:44:00,208 --> 00:44:02,978
Men are something else, aren't they?

673
00:44:02,978 --> 00:44:05,113
When it comes to raising kids,
they just watch from the sidelines.

674
00:44:05,113 --> 00:44:07,215
But they have plenty to say.

675
00:44:07,215 --> 00:44:10,185
They act like judges,
evaluating everything.

676
00:44:10,185 --> 00:44:12,921
They think they're some kind
of education experts.

677
00:44:23,532 --> 00:44:24,433
I've...

678
00:44:26,001 --> 00:44:27,736
never once slacked off.

679
00:44:29,538 --> 00:44:31,373
But in the end, all I get is,

680
00:44:33,341 --> 00:44:34,910
"You push too hard,"

681
00:44:36,678 --> 00:44:38,046
"Ease up a bit."

682
00:44:42,417 --> 00:44:44,119
Goodness.

683
00:44:44,119 --> 00:44:45,854
I'm saying too much.

684
00:44:48,690 --> 00:44:50,559
I've raised kids too. I understand.

685
00:44:51,493 --> 00:44:54,262
If not now, when would you
get to let it all out?

686
00:44:55,030 --> 00:44:57,532
You traveled a long way, so you don't
seem to have any friends here.

687
00:44:58,733 --> 00:45:00,836
Just think of this as a friend's house.

688
00:45:03,738 --> 00:45:05,941
Let's go to sleep now.

689
00:45:08,009 --> 00:45:10,345
I even brought you a fresh pillow.

690
00:45:12,581 --> 00:45:14,116
Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo.

691
00:45:14,583 --> 00:45:15,617
Good night.

692
00:45:30,198 --> 00:45:31,266
By the way,

693
00:45:32,267 --> 00:45:34,703
I think it's been about 30 years...

694
00:45:35,570 --> 00:45:37,506
since I slept over at a friend's house
like this.

695
00:45:40,375 --> 00:45:42,811
It feels like I've gone back
to middle school.

696
00:45:46,648 --> 00:45:48,350
Get some sleep.

697
00:45:49,618 --> 00:45:50,552
Okay.

698
00:46:11,106 --> 00:46:13,041
This is beef.

699
00:46:13,942 --> 00:46:14,910
Beef?

700
00:46:16,278 --> 00:46:17,646
Beef soup.

701
00:46:18,547 --> 00:46:21,583
Sweet potatoes are really sweet and good.

702
00:46:21,583 --> 00:46:23,385
Make sure your kids enjoy them.

703
00:46:23,385 --> 00:46:24,786
Okay. Thank you.

704
00:46:24,786 --> 00:46:26,021
Would you like some tea?

705
00:46:26,021 --> 00:46:26,888
No need.

706
00:46:28,523 --> 00:46:29,558
These are pancakes.

707
00:46:30,091 --> 00:46:32,194
They're not spicy
so your kids will like them.

708
00:46:34,663 --> 00:46:37,199
Thank you, but why...

709
00:46:38,834 --> 00:46:39,734
Just eat.

710
00:46:40,969 --> 00:46:42,904
- Thank you.
- You're here already?

711
00:46:43,572 --> 00:46:45,440
You are all so fast.

712
00:46:45,440 --> 00:46:46,341
What's that?

713
00:46:48,610 --> 00:46:51,379
- Hello.
- Hi, Ms. Seon Ja.

714
00:46:51,947 --> 00:46:53,248
These persimmons are really good.

715
00:46:54,349 --> 00:46:55,150
Here you go.

716
00:46:57,652 --> 00:47:00,355
I packed things that teenagers would love.

717
00:47:00,922 --> 00:47:02,691
Put them in the fridge and reheat them.

718
00:47:02,691 --> 00:47:03,992
They'll last you about a week.

719
00:47:05,093 --> 00:47:06,027
Thank you.

720
00:47:07,195 --> 00:47:09,798
Did words spread that my wife ran away?

721
00:47:11,133 --> 00:47:13,435
This is a town without secrets.

722
00:47:14,136 --> 00:47:15,237
I see.

723
00:47:15,871 --> 00:47:18,073
So everyone knows.

724
00:47:18,473 --> 00:47:20,142
I'm really ashamed.

725
00:47:20,642 --> 00:47:23,845
There may not be any secrets here,
but there is loyalty.

726
00:47:23,845 --> 00:47:25,413
Everyone's zipped their mouths.

727
00:47:28,917 --> 00:47:29,785
Hang in there.

728
00:47:31,186 --> 00:47:32,053
Thank you.

729
00:47:33,288 --> 00:47:35,157
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

730
00:47:38,326 --> 00:47:40,729
Cheon, Sang, and Gu. Come out. Let's eat.

731
00:47:51,873 --> 00:47:54,209
Where did all these come from?

732
00:47:55,577 --> 00:47:57,712
Did you use magic or something?

733
00:47:58,413 --> 00:48:00,215
Or did you hire a catering service?

734
00:48:01,249 --> 00:48:02,918
Wow. Kimchi pancakes.

735
00:48:02,918 --> 00:48:04,252
It looks good.

736
00:48:08,890 --> 00:48:09,825
It's so good.

737
00:48:11,760 --> 00:48:13,862
Dad, you can cook all this stuff too?

738
00:48:14,796 --> 00:48:17,999
Don't think about anything and just eat.

739
00:48:17,999 --> 00:48:19,000
We'll think after.

740
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:20,102
Eat up.

741
00:48:24,506 --> 00:48:25,907
My favorite.

742
00:48:31,213 --> 00:48:33,582
My youngest.

743
00:48:33,582 --> 00:48:34,516
Eat this.

744
00:48:54,136 --> 00:48:55,137
You're home.

745
00:48:57,773 --> 00:49:00,008
We got...

746
00:49:00,008 --> 00:49:02,377
new coffee beans at the cafe.

747
00:49:02,377 --> 00:49:03,478
You like coffee, don't you?

748
00:49:21,296 --> 00:49:24,766
They say food that looks good
tastes better.

749
00:49:24,766 --> 00:49:26,201
When it's presented nicely,

750
00:49:26,201 --> 00:49:28,036
it just feels better than eating casually.

751
00:49:39,948 --> 00:49:40,982
It's good.

752
00:49:41,616 --> 00:49:44,820
This tastes just like what I had
in Toronto.

753
00:49:44,820 --> 00:49:46,354
Did you make this?

754
00:49:47,823 --> 00:49:48,590
No.

755
00:49:49,224 --> 00:49:50,492
But it tastes good, doesn't it?

756
00:49:51,092 --> 00:49:53,728
These are my favorite desserts
at our cafe.

757
00:50:01,503 --> 00:50:02,604
Seong Ji Cheon.

758
00:50:03,839 --> 00:50:06,374
You've actually been coming here...

759
00:50:06,374 --> 00:50:08,143
and spending time with her?

760
00:50:08,844 --> 00:50:10,045
Mother, it's not like that...

761
00:50:10,045 --> 00:50:11,012
Hold on.

762
00:50:12,481 --> 00:50:14,416
I'll hear the details from my son.

763
00:50:24,459 --> 00:50:25,327
Well...

764
00:50:27,896 --> 00:50:29,064
The other day...

765
00:50:32,267 --> 00:50:35,137
I saw my son somewhere I never expected.

766
00:50:36,438 --> 00:50:39,574
So I kind of lost it.

767
00:50:39,574 --> 00:50:40,609
You were upset, weren't you?

768
00:50:42,010 --> 00:50:42,844
No.

769
00:50:43,612 --> 00:50:45,981
I was just...

770
00:50:45,981 --> 00:50:48,083
a little surprised.

771
00:50:48,083 --> 00:50:50,485
But you must've been really shocked,

772
00:50:50,485 --> 00:50:52,120
ma'am.

773
00:50:53,789 --> 00:50:54,990
Well...

774
00:50:54,990 --> 00:50:57,692
Just call me Ms. Cho.

775
00:51:01,830 --> 00:51:02,731
Okay.

776
00:51:03,765 --> 00:51:04,900
In due time.

777
00:51:07,269 --> 00:51:08,236
Bo Mi.

778
00:51:11,406 --> 00:51:12,507
The other day...

779
00:51:14,142 --> 00:51:15,110
I'm...

780
00:51:17,145 --> 00:51:18,313
sorry about how I acted.

781
00:51:22,484 --> 00:51:24,820
Thank you for being considerate.

782
00:51:25,487 --> 00:51:28,089
But I'm really okay.

783
00:51:28,790 --> 00:51:31,159
So please go ahead and enjoy
the fruits and desserts.

784
00:51:34,896 --> 00:51:36,031
Thanks.

785
00:51:36,031 --> 00:51:37,532
It's nothing.

786
00:51:53,248 --> 00:51:54,816
Sir, it's me.

787
00:51:55,851 --> 00:51:57,085
Hello, Mr. Jeong.

788
00:51:59,654 --> 00:52:00,489
What?

789
00:52:01,456 --> 00:52:02,390
You're where?

790
00:52:04,659 --> 00:52:06,595
Mr. Bae asked me to pass this along.

791
00:52:07,529 --> 00:52:09,598
The company hasn't been very supportive...

792
00:52:09,598 --> 00:52:11,566
of the Yeonri-ri branch until now.

793
00:52:12,968 --> 00:52:14,636
But recognizing your performance,

794
00:52:14,636 --> 00:52:17,706
he said to fully support you this time.

795
00:52:17,706 --> 00:52:18,940
No holding back.

796
00:52:20,709 --> 00:52:21,910
(Garden fertilizer)

797
00:52:21,910 --> 00:52:23,011
He said...

798
00:52:23,011 --> 00:52:25,113
your role in the first task
is extremely important.

799
00:52:26,581 --> 00:52:27,649
First task?

800
00:52:33,054 --> 00:52:35,690
This is top quality.

801
00:52:37,392 --> 00:52:38,426
It barely has any smell.

802
00:52:42,931 --> 00:52:44,299
There's no need to overthink it.

803
00:52:45,634 --> 00:52:47,169
Through your assignment,

804
00:52:47,169 --> 00:52:50,071
Yeonri-ri and Mat Story
will move toward mutual growth.

805
00:52:51,640 --> 00:52:54,509
You'll return to headquarters
by proving your loyalty,

806
00:52:55,177 --> 00:52:57,379
and the village will prosper
thanks to you.

807
00:53:00,482 --> 00:53:01,917
Maybe I shouldn't have
gotten suspicious of him.

808
00:53:04,286 --> 00:53:05,821
Mat Story?

809
00:53:06,021 --> 00:53:07,856
Chief. I'm glad you're here.

810
00:53:08,390 --> 00:53:11,026
These are supplies to support
the villagers.

811
00:53:11,593 --> 00:53:14,129
Support? That's ridiculous.
We're lucky it's not poison.

812
00:53:15,197 --> 00:53:16,865
Maybe this is just leftover stock
they're dumping on us.

813
00:53:20,202 --> 00:53:22,737
Your name is written on it.

814
00:53:22,737 --> 00:53:23,839
Is this your doing?

815
00:53:24,506 --> 00:53:27,309
You could say it's the first step...

816
00:53:27,809 --> 00:53:28,710
of the Yeonri-ri support project.

817
00:53:36,284 --> 00:53:37,185
Your feet.

818
00:53:38,520 --> 00:53:40,355
- Dad.
- Yes?

819
00:53:41,289 --> 00:53:42,157
Do you need something?

820
00:53:43,058 --> 00:53:44,659
I need to take my class.

821
00:53:45,560 --> 00:53:48,196
But today is a weekend.

822
00:53:48,830 --> 00:53:49,931
You're taking another class?

823
00:53:50,632 --> 00:53:52,601
I take an online class on Saturdays.

824
00:53:56,071 --> 00:53:58,707
I'm sure you need to log in
with Mom's account.

825
00:53:59,474 --> 00:54:01,076
I don't know her password.

826
00:54:02,911 --> 00:54:04,112
I don't either.

827
00:54:04,980 --> 00:54:07,482
Your mom is predictable.

828
00:54:07,482 --> 00:54:10,552
It's probably our anniversary
or one of your birthdays.

829
00:54:16,525 --> 00:54:17,425
Dad.

830
00:54:22,297 --> 00:54:23,265
(The password is incorrect)

831
00:54:23,265 --> 00:54:24,099
Dad.

832
00:54:29,538 --> 00:54:30,639
(The password is incorrect)

833
00:54:37,345 --> 00:54:39,614
That was the fourth attempt.

834
00:54:43,452 --> 00:54:44,853
(The password was incorrect five times)

835
00:54:45,020 --> 00:54:46,087
Dad.

836
00:54:47,923 --> 00:54:50,125
It starts at 11.

837
00:54:50,125 --> 00:54:52,127
I have to log in now.

838
00:54:52,928 --> 00:54:55,030
I'll call your mom.

839
00:55:05,607 --> 00:55:06,508
She's not answering.

840
00:55:10,645 --> 00:55:13,615
Today is a weekend.

841
00:55:13,615 --> 00:55:14,850
Why don't we have fun together?

842
00:55:16,351 --> 00:55:18,453
No, I want to take my class.

843
00:55:18,753 --> 00:55:21,523
It's my favorite CR class.

844
00:55:22,357 --> 00:55:23,859
Without Mom,

845
00:55:24,626 --> 00:55:26,394
the house is a total mess.

846
00:55:30,031 --> 00:55:32,901
I can't stand this chaos anymore.

847
00:55:32,901 --> 00:55:34,035
This is chaos.

848
00:55:35,470 --> 00:55:38,140
Dad, let's go find Mom. Please?

849
00:55:38,140 --> 00:55:39,541
Where is she?

850
00:55:39,541 --> 00:55:41,810
Dad, hurry.

851
00:55:41,810 --> 00:55:44,012
The class is about to start.

852
00:55:44,446 --> 00:55:46,648
Hurry, Dad.

853
00:55:46,648 --> 00:55:49,484
- Rock and roll.
- Hurry. Get up.

854
00:55:50,685 --> 00:55:52,053
Dad.

855
00:55:52,053 --> 00:55:53,789
It's 11 o'clock.

856
00:55:54,523 --> 00:55:58,560
Honey.

857
00:56:14,376 --> 00:56:15,744
Good grief.

858
00:56:16,978 --> 00:56:18,980
Did your late father come back?

859
00:56:20,248 --> 00:56:22,451
You look like you've aged ten years
in one day.

860
00:56:23,151 --> 00:56:25,220
Chief, I...

861
00:56:25,220 --> 00:56:26,388
You don't need to explain.

862
00:56:27,856 --> 00:56:30,292
I may not know much
about house chores either,

863
00:56:30,292 --> 00:56:32,160
but when it comes to kids,
the mom is always right.

864
00:56:32,160 --> 00:56:33,462
Mom is the law.

865
00:56:33,462 --> 00:56:34,863
I know, but...

866
00:56:35,530 --> 00:56:37,299
the house is a complete mess.

867
00:56:37,299 --> 00:56:40,402
There's no toothpaste.
I can't do anything.

868
00:56:40,402 --> 00:56:43,305
The fact that you can talk tells me
you still have a long way to go.

869
00:56:44,306 --> 00:56:46,108
Be patient and wait.
I'll give you a signal.

870
00:56:46,108 --> 00:56:47,809
Come by then and sincerely apologize.

871
00:56:48,577 --> 00:56:49,711
And...

872
00:56:52,180 --> 00:56:54,216
what are you going to do about
those fertilizer bags at the village hall?

873
00:56:54,216 --> 00:56:55,817
I didn't approve using those.

874
00:56:56,084 --> 00:56:57,552
Come on.

875
00:56:57,819 --> 00:57:00,255
The company just wants to work well
with Yeonri-ri.

876
00:57:00,255 --> 00:57:01,857
That's exactly the problem.

877
00:57:02,891 --> 00:57:04,025
Why would Mat Story do that?

878
00:57:04,826 --> 00:57:06,461
They're up to something.

879
00:57:06,461 --> 00:57:08,497
It's not like that.

880
00:57:11,466 --> 00:57:12,334
I've been...

881
00:57:13,235 --> 00:57:15,337
going out at dawn too, checking the soil,

882
00:57:16,004 --> 00:57:20,609
and pulling weeds one by one
with my own hands.

883
00:57:22,010 --> 00:57:25,313
If you slack off even a little,

884
00:57:25,313 --> 00:57:26,782
the soil shows it right away.

885
00:57:28,383 --> 00:57:31,219
Farming is really hard.

886
00:57:34,456 --> 00:57:35,791
You city boy.

887
00:57:36,625 --> 00:57:38,026
Did you think farming was easy?

888
00:57:38,593 --> 00:57:40,095
You do something this hard...

889
00:57:40,529 --> 00:57:44,132
every single day for a lifetime.

890
00:57:45,133 --> 00:57:46,768
I truly respect all of you.

891
00:57:48,336 --> 00:57:49,337
So...

892
00:57:50,138 --> 00:57:52,007
trust me just this once...

893
00:57:53,175 --> 00:57:55,410
and accept it. Okay?

894
00:57:59,815 --> 00:58:02,117
The fact that you're giving us fertilizer
first tells me you're a farmer now.

895
00:58:04,519 --> 00:58:07,255
You can go. I'll start
distributing it tomorrow.

896
00:58:07,255 --> 00:58:08,657
So don't be late in the morning.

897
00:58:08,657 --> 00:58:09,491
Are you serious?

898
00:58:12,961 --> 00:58:14,563
Thanks.

899
00:58:15,897 --> 00:58:17,299
Please tell Mi Ryeo...

900
00:58:17,699 --> 00:58:20,001
that we're doing okay.

901
00:58:21,269 --> 00:58:22,137
I'll tell her what I want to.

902
00:58:24,439 --> 00:58:27,042
Then tell her we're not doing well
without her.

903
00:58:28,009 --> 00:58:28,944
Go.

904
00:58:32,514 --> 00:58:36,151
(Free supply of premium fertilizer)

905
00:58:36,151 --> 00:58:38,220
(Mat Story win-win partnership,
Free supply of premium fertilizer)

906
00:58:38,220 --> 00:58:40,722
(Free supply of premium fertilizer)

907
00:58:41,857 --> 00:58:45,827
Yeonri-ri residents.
Mat Story is giving away...

908
00:58:45,827 --> 00:58:47,829
premium fertilizer for free.

909
00:58:47,829 --> 00:58:49,297
Please come quickly and pick it up.

910
00:58:49,297 --> 00:58:51,299
Yes, it's free. Take as much as you like.

911
00:58:51,299 --> 00:58:53,802
Yes, please come.

912
00:58:53,802 --> 00:58:56,505
Sign right here.

913
00:58:56,505 --> 00:58:57,472
Yes.

914
00:58:57,873 --> 00:58:59,641
Please come.

915
00:58:59,641 --> 00:59:02,410
Please come. This way.

916
00:59:03,411 --> 00:59:05,714
Yes, right here.

917
00:59:05,714 --> 00:59:08,150
- How many?
- Take two bags each.

918
00:59:08,150 --> 00:59:09,417
- Per household?
- Yes.

919
00:59:11,419 --> 00:59:12,687
(Free fertilizer distribution list
for Yeonri-ri branch)

920
00:59:12,687 --> 00:59:14,823
Yes, take as much as you want.

921
00:59:14,823 --> 00:59:16,691
Free fertilizer...

922
00:59:16,691 --> 00:59:20,829
directly provided by Manager Seong Tae Hun
from Mat Story.

923
00:59:21,496 --> 00:59:22,964
Come and get it.

924
00:59:22,964 --> 00:59:23,932
Two bags each.

925
00:59:25,000 --> 00:59:28,470
This is supported by Manager Seong Tae Hun
from Mat Story.

926
00:59:28,470 --> 00:59:30,672
Here are your names.
Deok Rae, Ok Rae, and Mak Rae.

927
00:59:31,773 --> 00:59:33,208
Seong Tae Hun of Mat Story.

928
00:59:34,876 --> 00:59:36,445
Two bags per household.

929
00:59:36,445 --> 00:59:37,779
Please take two each.

930
00:59:37,779 --> 00:59:39,114
Is it really okay to take this?

931
00:59:39,114 --> 00:59:40,649
Yes, it's fine.

932
00:59:40,649 --> 00:59:41,550
Have faith.

933
00:59:42,417 --> 00:59:44,820
Trust your village chief and take it.

934
00:59:44,820 --> 00:59:45,921
You're here.

935
00:59:45,921 --> 00:59:47,456
Thank you.

936
00:59:47,456 --> 00:59:50,058
I enjoyed the food you brought
the other day.

937
00:59:52,928 --> 00:59:54,329
Please take two each.

938
00:59:54,329 --> 00:59:55,831
Sign here.

939
00:59:56,298 --> 00:59:57,299
Thank you for your hard work.

940
00:59:59,301 --> 01:00:00,168
Here.

941
01:00:01,703 --> 01:00:02,537
Seong Tae Hun.

942
01:00:03,371 --> 01:00:04,272
Make sure you do this right.

943
01:00:05,273 --> 01:00:06,641
If you betray us again...

944
01:00:06,641 --> 01:00:09,311
or our cabbages die
because of that fertilizer,

945
01:00:09,611 --> 01:00:10,679
I won't forgive you.

946
01:00:13,281 --> 01:00:14,683
Take two.

947
01:00:14,683 --> 01:00:15,884
It's okay.

948
01:00:15,884 --> 01:00:17,352
Take as much as you want.

949
01:00:18,153 --> 01:00:20,322
Don't worry about anything,

950
01:00:20,322 --> 01:00:21,323
Chief.

951
01:00:23,492 --> 01:00:24,926
I still don't trust Mat Story.

952
01:00:25,627 --> 01:00:28,797
But I'm willing to trust you, Tae Hun.

953
01:00:32,367 --> 01:00:35,137
I didn't think the cabbages they trusted
would betray them.

954
01:00:37,205 --> 01:00:40,041
No. I just hoped they wouldn't.

955
01:00:42,711 --> 01:00:44,312
That's how trust always is.

956
01:00:49,384 --> 01:00:50,685
When you're holding it in your hands,

957
01:00:55,056 --> 01:00:56,558
you can't tell...

958
01:00:58,693 --> 01:00:59,661
whether it's poison...

959
01:01:01,363 --> 01:01:02,697
or medicine.

960
01:01:30,592 --> 01:01:33,528
(Cabbage Your Life)

961
01:01:33,528 --> 01:01:35,564
If you came to see your partner, go on in.

962
01:01:35,564 --> 01:01:36,665
I'll wait and see.

963
01:01:36,665 --> 01:01:37,833
Seon Ja, Dong Sik, and others...

964
01:01:37,833 --> 01:01:40,068
stopped by to give me food for the kids.

965
01:01:40,068 --> 01:01:41,403
Now that you've eaten this food,

966
01:01:41,403 --> 01:01:44,072
you've accepted everyone's kindness
in Yeonri-ri.

967
01:01:44,072 --> 01:01:46,274
I've caused trouble for you
and your family too.

968
01:01:46,274 --> 01:01:47,042
No.

969
01:01:47,042 --> 01:01:48,310
Right. I have something for you.

970
01:01:48,310 --> 01:01:49,211
Ta-da.

971
01:01:49,211 --> 01:01:50,245
Plant these seeds,

972
01:01:50,245 --> 01:01:52,747
and believe that happiness
is coming your way too.

973
01:01:52,747 --> 01:01:53,748
Marigold.

974
01:01:53,748 --> 01:01:54,816
What's this?

975
01:01:54,816 --> 01:01:56,051
Come out here quickly.

976
01:01:56,051 --> 01:01:57,452
What's all this about?

977
01:01:58,320 --> 01:02:00,088
The soil's gone bad.

978
01:02:00,088 --> 01:02:02,724
If I can buy you some time,
can you figure out what caused this?

979
01:02:02,724 --> 01:02:05,494
I'll be sure to restore those fields.

980
01:02:05,894 --> 01:02:07,896
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
